                            <comment id="43959" author="keith" created="Wed, 29 Aug 2012 13:26:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There is a patch to fix the all is green issue in master.  Please reopen if there is still an error. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="43590" author="keith" created="Tue, 21 Aug 2012 20:54:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#change,3591&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#change,3591&lt;/a&gt; is looking good for acceptance. &lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="42974" author="keith" created="Thu, 9 Aug 2012 18:07:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It looks as thought the test itself is working correctly but the /usr/bin/ part is not handling an ENOSPACE error correctly.  The systems are running out of desk space but the the /usr/bin/obdfilter-survey script does not pass the failure along.  I have added a flag to make the survey itself stop on an error and I am working on testing the change.  &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="42353" author="keith" created="Thu, 26 Jul 2012 19:22:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sorry for the delay. &lt;br/&gt;
I have submitted a possible fix for the always green issue: &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#change,3482&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#change,3482&lt;/a&gt;.  It needs to be tested but the return codes were not properly handled. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t quite understand the 2nd error &quot;2) echo client issue causing errors&quot;  Can you clarify what you mean? &lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="39065" author="pjones" created="Fri, 18 May 2012 13:05:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Keith&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Could you please look into this one?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Peter&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
